Citation.sTitle: Thermophysical study of the binary mixtures of N,N-dimethylacetamide with 2-propanol and 2-butanol
Citation.sAbstract: This work reports thermophysical properties measurements of binary mixtures of N,N-dimethylacetamide with 2-propanol and 2-butanol. Density, n, speed of sound, u, refractive index, nD, and kinematic viscosity, i, were measured over the whole composition range at the temperatures (283.15, 298.15 and 313.15) K and at atmospheric pressure p=0.1 MPa. Experimental data were used to calculate the following properties: excess molar volume, VE, excess isentropic compressibility, eS E,refractive index deviation, AnD, and viscosity deviation, Ac. These properties were correlated with the Redlich-Kister equation. Excess molar volumes were positive for both mixtures. Refractive index deviations were positive for N,N-dimethylacetamide +2-propanol and negative for N,N-dimethylacetamide + 2-butanol. Excess isentropic compressibilities and viscosity deviations were negative for the two systems. Finally, the results obtained were interpreted based on both structural and energetic effects.
